Hey there! I got you covered with a cool and trendy HTML table for your food blog. Let's create a stylish table with 4 columns and 4 rows using rowspan and colspan to make it visually appealing.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Delicious Food Blog</title>
<style>
    table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
    }
    th, td {
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        padding: 15px;
        text-align: left;
    }
    th {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
    }
    .highlight {
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Trendy Food Table</h2>

<table>
    <tr>
        <th colspan="4">Yummy Recipes</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td rowspan="2">Breakfast</td>
        <td>Eggs Benedict</td>
        <td>Avocado Toast</td>
        <td class="highlight">Smoothie Bowl</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td colspan="2">Pancakes & Berries</td>
        <td>French Toast</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Lunch</td>
        <td>Caesar Salad</td>
        <td class="highlight" rowspan="2">Sushi Platter</td>
        <td>Caprese Sandwich</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Dinner</td>
        <td>Grilled Salmon</td>
        <td>Vegetable Stir-Fry</td>
        <td class="highlight">Steak & Potatoes</td>
    </tr>
</table>

</body>
</html>
```

This HTML code creates a stylish and trendy table for your food blog, showcasing various delicious recipes for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. The creative use of rowspan and colspan adds a visually appealing layout to your content. Feel free to customize the recipes and design further to match your blog's style! Enjoy sharing your culinary delights with your readers.
